This function is a standalone program and doesn't require any extra-packages installation. 

Although it depends on some basic python libraries inculding
a) Matplotlib b) Numpy c) Scipy

This software is tested on both python 2.7 and 3.6. 

In case, you don't have above libraries, please install as follows: 
--------------
Linux users:
--------------
python -m pip install numpy scipy matplotlib 
or 
python3 -m pip install numpy scipy matplotlib      (if you want to use python3)  
or 
pip3 install numpy scipy matplotlib 
------------
Mac-Users
------------
brew tap homebrew/science && brew install python numpy scipy matplotlib
or 
brew tap homebrew/science && brew install python3 numpy scipy matplotlib

If you don't have brew, please copy paste the follwoing command in terminal:
ruby -e "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/master/install)"


